  "body": "Per [this provider-engine issue](https://github.com/MetaMask/provider-engine/issues/176#issuecomment-325559955), some users want to use things like provider engine to deploy their contracts in a custom way, and provider engine requires a `.stop()` call to deallocate some event listeners.\r\n\r\nTruffle could add an optional `after_deploy` key on the `truffle.js` exports that would be called after contracts were deployed, where devs could do cleanup like this.",
