    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "It sounds to me like the `engine` is keeping the process open, perhaps with a timer that's not properly dereferenced? Once the deploy has finished, Truffle attempts to quit -- or at least it should, if nothing keeps the process open. Timeouts and intervals can keep the process open in Node. \n\nIf this is the case for the provider engine, perhaps you can use [timeout.unref()](https://nodejs.org/api/timers.html#timers_timeout_unref) to ensure it doesn't keep the process going:\n\n```\nvar timeout_id = setTimeout(function() {...}, 1000);\n\n// Check for the existence of `unref` so code is portable to the browser.\nif (timeout_id.unref) {\n  timeout_id.unref();\n}\n```\n\nThis will ensure the process doesn't stay open after deploys.",
